# Basketball Platform â€” Frontend API Guide

## Base URL
All endpoints are prefixed with `/api`.
- **Local Dev**: `http://localhost:3000/api`
- **Production**: `https://your-render-url.onrender.com/api`

---

## Authentication

All endpoints (except login/register) require a **Bearer token** in the `Authorization` header.

```
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```

### Login
**POST** `/api/auth/login`
```json
{ "email": "admin@example.com", "password": "password123" }
```
Response includes `user.name` (use this for the welcome message):
```json
{
  "access_token": "...",
  "user": { "id": "...", "email": "...", "name": "John Doe", "role": "ADMIN" }
}
```

> **Roles**: `SUPER_ADMIN`, `ADMIN`, `STATISTICIAN`

---

## Role-Based Access Rules

| Tab / Feature | Who Can See It |
|---|---|
| **Users Tab** (create/delete admins) | `SUPER_ADMIN` only |
| Players, Teams, Tournaments, Matches | `ADMIN` + `STATISTICIAN` |
| Delete operations | `ADMIN` only |
| Statistician workspace | Own separate UI (not admin) |

---

## Image Uploads (Team Logo, Player Photo)

All images go through a **two-step process**:
1. **Upload the file â†’ get a URL**
2. **Save the URL in the entity**

### Step 1 â€” Upload File
**POST** `/api/upload`
- Content-Type: `multipart/form-data`
- Field name: `file`

Response:
```json
{ "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/...", "public_id": "..." }
```

### Step 2 â€” Save URL
Pass the returned `url` as the `logo` (for teams) or `photo` (for players) field when creating or updating:

**PATCH /api/teams/:id** â†’ `{ "logo": "https://res.cloudinary.com/..." }`

**PATCH /api/players/:id** â†’ `{ "photo": "https://res.cloudinary.com/..." }`

---

## Players

### Get All Players
**GET** `/api/players`

| Query Param | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `teamId` | string | Filter to players on a specific team |
| `unassigned` | `"true"` | **NEW** â€” Returns only players with NO active team. Use this for the "Add Player" dropdown in Teams tab |

### Update Player (Edit Modal)
**PATCH** `/api/players/:id`

You can now also update jersey number in one request by including `teamId`:
```json
{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "photo": "https://res.cloudinary.com/...",
  "teamId": "team-uuid-here",
  "jerseyNumber": 23
}
```

### Merge Duplicate Players
**POST** `/api/players/merge`
```json
{ "duplicatePlayerId": "...", "targetPlayerId": "..." }
```

---

## Teams

### Get All Teams
**GET** `/api/teams`

| Query Param | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `tournamentId` | string | **NEW** â€” Returns only teams registered in that tournament. Use this for Home/Away dropdowns when creating a match |

### Set Team Captain
**PATCH** `/api/teams/:teamId/players/:playerId/captain`
```json
{ "isCaptain": true }
```
> Setting `isCaptain: true` automatically removes captain status from any other player on that team.

---

## Tournaments

### Tournament Divisions (exact enum values)

| Value | Label |
|---|---|
| `PREMIER` | Premier Division |
| `DIVISION_1` | Division 1 |
| `DIVISION_2` | Division 2 |
| `DIVISION_3` | Division 3 |

### Create Tournament
**POST** `/api/tournaments`
```json
{
  "name": "Spring League 2025",
  "division": "PREMIER",
  "numberOfGames": 10,
  "quarterDuration": 10,
  "startDate": "2025-03-01"
}
```

---

## Bulk Upload Players (Excel/CSV)

**POST** `/api/players/team/:teamId/upload`
- Content-Type: `multipart/form-data`, field name: `file`

**Required columns** (column order doesn't matter):

| Column Header | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `First Name` | âś… | |
| `Last Name` | âś… | |
| `Email` | Optional | Used for deduplication |
| [Height](file:///c:/Users/USER/Documents/GitHub/basketball-be/src/common/services/player-deduplication.service.ts#266-290) | Optional | e.g. `6'2"` |
| `Phone` | Optional | |
| `Date of Birth` | Optional | ISO format: `YYYY-MM-DD` |
| `Nationality` | Optional | |
| `Jersey Number` | Optional | |
| `Position` | Optional | `POINT_GUARD`, `SHOOTING_GUARD`, `SMALL_FORWARD`, `POWER_FORWARD`, `CENTER` |
| `Gender` | Optional | e.g. `Male`, `Female` |

**Response** includes:
- `created`: number of new players created
- `duplicatesFound`: number skipped/flagged
- `details`: array with per-row actions (`CREATED`, `LINKED`, `ALREADY_IN_TEAM`, `SKIPPED`)
- `errors`: rows that failed with reasons

---

## Matches

### Create Match
**POST** `/api/matches`
> Use `GET /api/teams?tournamentId=<id>` to get valid home/away team options!

```json
{
  "tournamentId": "...",
  "homeTeamId": "...",
  "awayTeamId": "...",
  "scheduledDate": "2025-03-15T19:30:00Z"
}
```
> âš ď¸Ź Always send `scheduledDate` in **UTC** (append `Z` or include timezone offset) to avoid the 1-hour display shift.

### Match Status Values

| Value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `SCHEDULED` | Default |
| `LIVE` | In progress |
| `COMPLETED` | Finished |
| `CANCELLED` | Cancelled |
| `POSTPONED` | Rescheduled |
